quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,11,"[Imagine] how many towns of wrongdoers We have destroyed<sup>6</sup>, and raised after them another people!","[6] i.e., who were persisting in wrongdoing."
  21,12,"When they sensed Our punishment, they started running away from it.",""
  21,13,"“Do not run away, but return to your luxuries and dwellings<sup>7</sup>, perhaps you will be questioned.”","[7] This is said to them in sarcasm and ridicule."
  21,14,"They said, “Woe to us! We were indeed wrongdoers.”",""
  21,15,"They kept crying this out loud until We mowed them down, lifeless<sup>8</sup>.","[8] i.e., extinguished like ashes."
  21,16,"We did not create the heavens and earth and all that is between them for fun.",""
  21,17,"If We had wished for a pastime<sup>9</sup>, We could have had it from Our own, if We were to do so.","[9] Such as a wife or a child."
  21,18,"Rather, We hurl the truth at falsehood, and it crushes it<sup>10</sup>, so it vanishes. Woe to you for what you falsely ascribe [to Allah]<sup>11</sup>!","[10] Lit. ""strikes its brain,"" disabling or killing it.\n [11] Claiming that He has a son, a wife, or a partner."
  21,19,"To Him belongs all those who are in the heavens and earth. Those [angels] who are with Him are not too proud to worship Him, nor do they ever grow weary.",""
  21,20,"They glorify Him day and night tirelessly.",""
  21,21,"Or have they taken gods from the earth who [cannot even] resurrect the dead?",""
  21,22,"If there had been gods besides Allah in the heavens and earth, both realms would have fallen in disorder. Glory be to Allah – Lord of the Throne – far above what they ascribe [to Him].",""
  21,23,"He cannot be questioned for what He does, but they will be questioned.",""
  21,24,"Or have they taken other gods besides Him? Say, “Bring your proof. Here is the Book of those who are with me, and the Book of those who came before me<sup>12</sup>.” Yet most of them do not know the truth, so they turn away.","[12] The Prophet (ﷺ) is addressed to challenge the pagans to produce their proof for the existence of other gods; whereas, the Qur’an, the Torah, and the Gospel are in agreement that there is no god but Allah alone."
